Wild One The Very Best Of - Thin Lizzy [1996]


Wild One: The Very Best of Thin Lizzy - is a 1996 compilation album by Irish rock band Thin Lizzy. It was released ten years after the death of frontman Phil Lynott in 1986, and as a tribute to him.
Although its title is shared by a Thin Lizzy song (Wild One), and also quotes the chorus of the song on the back of the album, the song itself is actually only included on the limited 2CD edition of the album, which contains a rare live concert.
